```javascript
function checkPrimes(arr) {
  let isPrime = false;
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    let num = parseInt(arr[i]);
    if (isPrime || num < 2) continue; // Skip if already printed or less than 2 (not a number)
    let isPrimeNum = true;
    for (let j = 2; j <= Math.sqrt(num); j++) {
      if (num % j === 0) {
        isPrimeNum = false;
        break;
      }
    }
    if (isPrimeNum) {
      console.log(arr[i]);
      isPrime = true; // Update flag for next iteration
    }
  }
}
```

To use this function, you can pass an array of 5 numbers as an argument:

```javascript
